text: Saba Lobzhanidze (, ; born 18 December 1994) is a Georgian footballer who currently plays for Turkish club Ankaragücü.Randers henter målfarlig georgier‚ bold.dk, 22 June 2017 ==Club career== Born in Tbilisi, Lobzhanidze started playing for Norchi Dinamoeli at the age of 10. Later he joined Dinamo Tbilisi. In summer 2017, Lobzhanidze signed a three-year contract with Randers. ==International career== Lobzhanidze made his debut for the Georgia national football team on 23 January 2017 in a friendly against Uzbekistan, scoring one of the two goals of his team. ===International goals=== :Scores and results list Georgia's goal tally first. {| class="wikitable" style="font-size:100%;" !
